.TH splitclm 1  "USER COMMANDS"
.SH NAME
splitclm \- copy specific bands of clm data files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B splitclm
[\-h] [\-longheader] first last
\fIinfile\fP \fIoutfile\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
Program copies specific bands from data files in clm format.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-h,\--help
Print a short help text.
.TP
\-longheader
Long (version 2) header assumed for clm files.
.TP
first
Index of first band to be copied into new file. Index starts from 1.
.TP
last
Index of last band to be copied into new file. Index stars from 1.
.TP
.I infile
Filename(s) of clm files to be cut.
.TP
.I outfile
Filename of new clm file.
.SH EXAMPLE
.TP
Create clm data file copying bands 10-12:
.B splitclm
10 12 temp.clm temp_OND.clm
.PP
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B splitclm
returns a zero exit status if the clm file is created.
Non zero is returned in case of failure.

